Title: A Note on Using 32-Bit CRC for Detecting Cell Misordering in ATM Networks  
Author: Zheng Wang Jon Crowcroft 
Address: London WC1E 6BT, United Kingdom  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science, University College London  
Abstract: In the simple and efficient adaptation layer (SEAL) proposal, a 32-bit CRC is used for error check for the entire frame. In this note, we analyze the performance of the 32-bit CRC used in SEAL for detecting cell misordering. Our results show that the 32-bit CRC provides a robust detection of cell misordering. For any frame size upto 4 Gbits, the probability of undetected misordering is 2 32 (approximately 2:33 fi 10 10 ). 
